Active Directory JML Automation (Joiner–Mover–Leaver)
Overview

This project simulates a real-world Identity and Access Management (IAM) workflow in an Active Directory environment.

The script automates the lifecycle of user accounts based on HR input data:

Joiners → create and provision new users
Movers → update department, OU, and group memberships
Leavers → disable accounts

It is designed to be idempotent, auditable, and safe to re-run, mirroring production automation practices.

Key Features:
-Automated user provisioning from CSV input
-Organizational Unit (OU) placement based on department
-Role-based group assignment and reconciliation
-Account lifecycle management (create, update, disable)
-Structured logging (text + JSON for audit/reporting)
-Dry-run mode for safe testing
-Error handling with clear operational feedback

Project Structure
├── Invoke-JML.ps1        # Main automation script
├── users.csv             # Sample HR input file
├── logs/                 # Execution logs + JSON reports
├── docs/                 # Architecture and setup notes
└── screenshots/          # ADUC, GPO, and environment visuals

How It Works

1. HR exports a CSV containing user lifecycle events
2. Script processes each record based on Status:
3. Joiner → creates user, assigns OU + groups
4. Mover → updates OU and reconciles group membership
5. Leaver → disables account

All actions are logged for traceability

Sample Input (users.csv)

Dry Run (recommended first):
.\Invoke-JML.ps1 -CsvPath .\users.csv -DryRun

Execute Changes:
.\Invoke-JML.ps1 -CsvPath .\users.csv

Example Output:
Text log: logs/jml-<timestamp>.log
JSON report: logs/jml-<timestamp>.json

These logs provide a full audit trail of:

Actions taken
Errors encountered
Changes applied to each user
Design Considerations
Idempotency: Safe to re-run without duplicating users
Separation of concerns: Config (OU/group mapping) separated from logic
Auditability: Structured logs for review and compliance
Scalability: Easily extended for additional departments or roles

This project is a lab simulation and does not include production security hardening. It is intended to demonstrate automation patterns and Active Directory administration concepts.